SCENE STRUCTURE GUIDANCE
=========================
Child-custody cases generate extreme emotion — fear and aggression are intertwined:
  1. Session start — parent is informed of the welfare assessment or removal risk.
  2. Denial — parent denies the allegations or assessment; becomes defensive.
  3. Emotional escalation — fear for child transforms into anger at the system and the worker.
  4. Accusation — parent accuses worker of bias, incompetence, or malice.
  5. Explicit threat — parent threatens legal action, personal consequences, or physical harm.
The worker must remain calm and professional while documenting and de-escalating.

